[How to execute RESTFUL API to configure TG embedded system:]

Prerequisite: To get the TG embedded system ready, please refer to the document 
https://github.com/TGautomation/non_contact_measurement/blob/cba7557764ffe0113af6f7ea7729ebf9dbe2854e/user_guide/SOP/How%20to%20invoke%20the%20embedded%20system%20server....

This document is to illustrate how to use standard GET/SET operations to configure the TG embedded measurement system.

The embedded system is run in a hardware box called i.MX8.  Power on i.MX8.
Connect to i.MX8 through a serial cable.
Or through Tera Term (5) or puTTY, open a terminal.
In the terminal, login as user: root, no password.  All commands are issued as dot+space+command.

In one terminal, type "cd /opt/tglobal/simulation" and HIT ENTER to reach the operation directory.   Then type ". start_engine.sh" and hit ENTER to start the TG embedded measurement system.
In another terminal, run the self test to demonstrate GET/SET operations for configuring the embedded system.
Type ". self-test-config-api-get.sh" and hit ENTER to perform self-test demonstration of GET operations.
Type ". self-test-config-api-set.sh" and hit ENTER to perform self-test demonstration of GET operations.


Access the server to configure the system through the following ways:
1. Browser with URL http://172.16.14.61:3000/trigger/config/ plus the intended configuration operation and item. Synopsis follows in the self-tests.
2. Linux/Unix/iOS terminal: type "curl -s http://172.16.14.61:3000/trigger/config/ plus the request data meta data sub-URL.  Synopsis follows in self-test.
3. For individual test item execution using a browser, taking tj_tc_delta as an illustration, type "http://172.14.16.62:3000/trigger/config/get/tj_tc_delta in the browser.
4. For individual test item execution using a terminal, taking tj_tc_delta as an illustration, type "curl -s http://172.14.16.61:3000/trigger/config/get/Tj_tc_delta" in the terminal.

Demonstration commands:
Type ". start_engine.sh" in one terminal.
Type ". self-test-config-api-get.sh" in another terminal for GET operations.
Type ". self-test-config-api-set.sh" in another terminal for GET operations.

Additional commands:
cd -- change directory
ls -al -- list current directory.

